    <div class="eyebrow a a1">The solution — three signal layers</div>
    <div class="l-heavy">
      <div>
        <div class="display a a2" style="font-size:40px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:8px;line-height:1.1">The vibe signal already exists everywhere. We just organized it.</div>
        <div class="body a a3" style="font-size:14px;margin-bottom:24px">Vibe Check doesn't create new data. It aggregates three types of signals that already exist publicly and organizes them into one real-time mood-matched decision layer.</div>
        <div class="a a4">
          <div class="layer">
            <div class="layer-num">1</div>
            <div class="layer-body">
              <div class="layer-title">Recent public content — the feel signal</div>
              <div class="layer-desc">Publicly tagged TikToks and Instagram Reels from the last 24–72 hours. Already public, already consented to. Curated for atmosphere over faces — wide shots of crowd, lighting, energy. Labelled clearly as "shot by real visitors, not the venue."</div>
              <div><span class="layer-tag">Visual</span><span class="layer-tag">Emotional</span><span class="layer-tag">Authentic</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="layer">
