<!-- SLIDE 15: REWARDS DECISION -->
<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="slide" id="s14">
  <div class="slide-tag">Product Decision · Rewards</div>
  <div class="slide-inner">
    <div class="eyebrow a a1">Key product decision — rewards system design</div>
    <div class="display a a2" style="font-size:38px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:12px">4 attempts. Each one taught us something different.</div>
    <div class="body a a3" style="font-size:14px;margin-bottom:20px;max-width:900px">The rewards system was the hardest design problem in Vibe Check. The core tension: <strong style="color:var(--text)">users contribute content to earn rewards, but how you structure rewards changes how people behave — and can either reinforce good habits or incentivize gaming the system.</strong> Here's every attempt we made and why each one failed before we got it right.</div>
    <div class="two-col">
      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:10px" class="a a3">
        <div class="card" style="padding:16px 20px;border-left:3px solid var(--red)">
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;margin-bottom:6px"><span style="font-size:14px">✗</span><div style="font-size:14px;font-weight:500;color:var(--text)">Attempt 1: Single points — spend to redeem</div></div>
          <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--text3);line-height:1.5">Problem: if your rank is based on total points and you spend points on rewards, redeeming a free cocktail literally lowers your status in the app. Users noticed immediately — "why would I spend if it makes me look less active?" The system punishes engagement. Rejected.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card" style="padding:16px 20px;border-left:3px solid var(--red)">
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;margin-bottom:6px"><span style="font-size:14px">✗</span><div style="font-size:14px;font-weight:500;color:var(--text)">Attempt 2: Milestone unlocks with 30-day expiry</div></div>
          <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--text3);line-height:1.5">Points go up, rewards unlock at thresholds, but each reward expires in 30 days if unclaimed. Problem: expiry still felt like a penalty. And from the venue side — how do you operationalise a reward that's only valid for 30 days? Adds friction for partners. Rejected.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card" style="padding:16px 20px;border-left:3px solid var(--red)">
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;margin-bottom:6px"><span style="font-size:14px">✗</span><div style="font-size:14px;font-weight:500;color:var(--text)">Attempt 3: Streak system (like Duolingo)</div></div>
          <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--text3);line-height:1.5">Weekly contribution streak unlocks rewards. Sounds clean — but a week is long enough that anyone can game it. No quality check means users upload old screenshots or random photos just to keep the streak alive. The incentive creates the exact behaviour we don't want. Rejected.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card" style="padding:16px 20px;border-left:3px solid var(--gold);background:var(--gold3)">
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;margin-bottom:6px"><span style="font-size:14px;color:var(--gold)">✓</span><div style="font-size:14px;font-weight:500;color:var(--gold)">Attempt 4: Two currencies — final solution</div></div>
          <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--text2);line-height:1.6">Two completely separate currencies. Vibe Points = your XP and identity in the app — goes up with every action, defines your rank (Explorer → Local → Insider → Vibe Authority), never spent on anything. Vibe Coins = your spendable wallet — also earned per action, but used exclusively for rewards. Redeeming a free cocktail costs 80 coins. Your point total stays exactly where it was. Your rank never changes. In round 2 testing, every user understood this split immediately — no explanation needed.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="a a4">
        <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--text3);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;margin-bottom:12px">Every action earns both currencies simultaneously</div>
        <div class="card" style="padding:18px 22px">
