<!-- SLIDE 16: CONSTRAINTS & TRADEOFFS -->
<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="slide" id="s15">
  <div class="slide-tag">Constraints & Tradeoffs</div>
  <div class="slide-inner">
    <div class="eyebrow a a1">Constraints &amp; tradeoffs — what I had to solve before building</div>
    <div class="display a a2" style="font-size:38px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:28px">Three hard problems. Three real solutions.</div>
    <div class="three-col">
      <div class="card a a3" style="padding:22px 24px">
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--red);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;margin-bottom:10px">Challenge 1</div>
        <div style="font-size:16px;font-weight:500;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:8px">Privacy &amp; live content</div>
        <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text3);margin-bottom:16px;line-height:1.5">Original idea: show live clips of places. Problem: businesses won't give camera access. Filming patrons in real time without consent is a legal and ethical issue.</div>
        <div class="hr-gold"></div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;margin-bottom:8px">Resolution</div>
        <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text2);line-height:1.5">We only surface content that is already public and legally shareable — no scraping, no taking content without permission. Two clean sources: Google Places API for live crowd data (fully anonymised and within their terms), and user-uploaded content posted directly to Vibe Check. Users can also link their Instagram, Snapchat, or TikTok accounts to cross-post their vibe clips — they consent explicitly at that point. Content we surface always credits the original poster.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card a a4" style="padding:22px 24px">
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--red);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;margin-bottom:10px">Challenge 2</div>
        <div style="font-size:16px;font-weight:500;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:8px">Third-party data access</div>
        <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text3);margin-bottom:16px;line-height:1.5">TikTok Research API: academic institutions only. Instagram Graph API: largely shut down post-Cambridge Analytica. Can't pull public location-tagged content at scale commercially.</div>
        <div class="hr-gold"></div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;margin-bottom:8px">Resolution</div>
        <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text2);line-height:1.5">Phase 1: embed model. Phase 2: creator partnerships (opted-in creators share across platforms). Phase 3: Vibe Check becomes primary destination — Vibe Coins make uploading here more valuable than Instagram.</div>
      </div>
